This paper discusses distance metric learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that deals with learning distances between data points. The paper focuses on classification and dimensionality reduction, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses mathematical foundations, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.SD). Finally, the paper presents a Python package for implementing the discussed techniques, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, which is the primary subfield of machine learning, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.SD.
